.TH "omap_cm_module_disable" 9 "omap_cm_module_disable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap_cm_module_disable \- disable a module
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" omap_cm_module_disable
.BI "(u8 part "  ","
.BI "u16 inst "  ","
.BI "u16 clkctrl_offs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "part" 12
PRCM partition
.IP "inst" 12
PRCM instance
.IP "clkctrl_offs" 12
CM_CLKCTRL register offset for the module
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Disables clocks for a module identified by (\fIpart\fP, \fIinst\fP, \fIclkctrl_offs\fP)
makings its IO space inaccessible. Return 0 upon success, -EINVAL if
no per-SoC \fBmodule_disable\fP function pointer has been registered.
